    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a bit of a mixed bag then. But if we're looking at the long term, wouldn't you say the whole thing was fundamentally a failure? I mean, the regime is gone, but the country is basically a failed state now and the region is way more unstable. It seems like the cost of the intervention was way higher than any of the supposed benefits.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
